miscConds.notes:
During the pendency of this deferral, the Defendant agrees to:
-Commit no acts which rise to the level of probable cause in violation of the criminal laws of the state of Wisconsin, or of any other state, or of the United States of America.
-Comply with all conditions of bail or bond in this case.
-Pay a fine of 50.00 plus costs (to be assessed on count 2) within four months from the date this agreement is accepted unless a payment plan is agreed to by the Clerk of Courts.
-Comply with all conditions of probation relative to count 2 in this matter. Violation of any rule of probation, or revocation from probation, constitutes a violation of this condition. 
-The parties agree, and the defendant understands, that the conditions of any bail or bond in effect on the plea date shall continue for the entire length of this agreement, and that any violation of the defendant's bond may result in bail jumping charges pursuant to Wis. Stat. 946.49. The defendant further understands that a charged violation of the bail or bond for which probable cause is found shall be a basis for the State to vacate this agreement.
-Defendant will keep Douglas County Clerk of Courts informed of his address and telephone number at all times, and stipulates that the sending of notice by regular mail to the address on file with the Clerk of Courts constitutes sufficient notice of any court hearings scheduled in this matter.  The non-appearance of the defendant may result in the issuance of an arrest warrant. 
-If, at any time during the deferral period, the defendant has no complied with the conditions of this agreement, the State may at its discretion and upon notice the defendant, revoke the agreement and move the Court to enter judgment of conviction and the parties shall proceed to sentencing. At sentencing, the State shall be free to argue for any disposition it deems appropriate, up to and including the maximum sentence provided by law.

-Except as otherwise provided in this agreement, the State must prove non-compliance with thus agreement by the preponderance of the evidence at a hearing subject to Wis. Stat. 911.01(4)(c). 
-At the end of this deferral period or upon completion of all terms of this agreement, whichever is later, if the defendant has complied with the conditions of this agreement and provided proof of compliance when required, the State will move to amend count 1 to reflect a violation of misdemeanor battery, as an act of domestic abuse, contrary to Wis. Stat. 940.19(1), 968.075, with no further penalty beyond any jail time served and financial obligation already paid.

records.addlTxt: Letters from DCC Records staff to Court regarding sentence structure
Conditions of no contact with Victim and No use or possession of alcohol.

9:56 AM Defendant Jayden Manthey in court.  Attorney Stephen Robert Zuber in court for Jayden Manthey.  Attorney Mark Adam Fruehauf in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls case. State recites agreement. Defendant will plead to counts 1 and 2. Judgment of conviction will be deferred pursuant to the agreement in count 1. Count 2, sentence will be withheld in favor of 2 years or probation. Conditions of $50 fine plus costs, 2 days jail with credit for 2 days, and DOC programming. Attorney Zuber asks that the bail be modified to a signature bond with amended conditions. 
Defendant pleads no contest to both counts, with modifiers. Attorney Zuber stipulates to a factual basis. Court accepts the defendant's pleas and finds that the pleas have been freely and intelligently made. 
Court defers judgment of conviction on count 1 pursuant to the agreement. 
Court orders on count 2, sentence withheld for 2 years or probation. Conditions of $50 fine plus costs, 2 days jail with credit for 2 days, and DOC programming.
Court amends bond to signature bond. Conditions of no contact with Victim and No use or possession of alcohol.

9:08 AM Defendant Jayden Manthey in court.  Attorney Stephen Robert Zuber in court for Jayden Manthey.  Attorney Mark Adam Fruehauf in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney acknowledges receipt of the information, waives a formal reading, enters a plea of not guilty and requests a status. Court accepts pleas. State has no objection to another status.
Status conference scheduled for September 26, 2022 at 09:00 am.
